[src:capacity-planning/capacity-management] This capacity planning identifies any potential capacity related issues likely to arise, and justifies any necessary investment decisions - for example, the server requirements to accommodate future IT resource demand, or a data center consolidation.
[src:capacity-planning/capacity-management] These activities are intended to optimize performance and efficiency, and to plan for and justify financial investments.
[src:capacity-planning/capacity-management] Capacity management interacts with the discipline of Performance Engineering, both during the requirements and design activities of building a system, and when using performance monitoring.
[src:capacity-planning/capacity-management] As data is broken into component parts (often known frames, packets, or segments) for transmission, several factors can affect their delivery.
[src:capacity-planning/capacity-management] These factors, and others (such as the performance of the network signaling on the end nodes, compression, encryption, concurrency, and so on) all affect the effective performance of a network.
